.TH LPF-DIFF 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-diff \- show the delta between current host state and a plan
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf diff [\-\-backend nftables] [\-\-observed <ruleset>|\-\-live] [\-\-json] <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compare a generated plan with current lpf\-owned host state.
The current implementation reads live nftables state by default, extracts lpf\-owned table blocks, and compares them with rendered intent.
Supplying \-\-observed reads nftables ruleset text from a file or stdin for deterministic tests.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-backend nftables
select nftables diffing; currently the only backend
.TP
\-\-observed <ruleset>
read observed nftables ruleset text from a file or \- for stdin
.TP
\-\-live
read observed nftables ruleset text with `nft list ruleset`; this is the default
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable nftables diff status and text
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf diff /etc/lpf.conf
lpf diff \-\-observed current.nft fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
lpf diff \-\-json /etc/lpf.conf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-plan(8), lpf\-rules(8)
